As part of the continuing work to replace 1-element arrays in the Linux kernel, it&#8217;s very handy to show that a source change has had no executable code difference. For example, if you started with this:

struct foo {
    unsigned long flags;
    u32 length;
    u32 data[1];
};

void foo_init(int count)
{
    struct foo *instance;
    size_t bytes = sizeof(*instance) + sizeof(u32) * (count - 1);
    ...
    instance = kmalloc(bytes, GFP_KERNEL);
    ...
};

And you changed on...
